---
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';

// TODO(client): have counsel review before launch (see README pre-launch list).
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Use — Reliant Construction"
  description="The terms that govern your use of the Reliant Construction website, including estimates, proposals, and intellectual property."
  heading="Terms of use"
  effective="July 12, 2026"
>
  <p>
    These terms govern your use of this website, operated by {site.legalName} ("Reliant
    Construction," "we," "us"). By using the site, you agree to them. If you don't agree,
    please don't use the site.
  </p>

  <div>
    <h2>The website is information, not a contract</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Content on this site — service descriptions, process explanations, photography, and
      example figures — is provided for general information. It is not an offer, and nothing
      on this site creates a contract between you and Reliant Construction. Construction
      services are provided only under a signed written agreement that describes the specific
      scope, price, schedule, and warranty for your project.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Estimates and proposals</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Free estimates and fixed-price proposals described on this site are subject to a site
      walkthrough and written confirmation. A proposal becomes binding only when both parties
      sign it. Response and turnaround times described on this site are service goals, not
      guarantees, and may vary with project size and complexity.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Warranties</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Workmanship and material warranties referenced on this site are summaries. The
      controlling warranty terms — coverage, duration, transferability, exclusions, and claim
      procedures — are those set out in your signed project agreement and warranty documents.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Photography and project imagery</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Some imagery on this site is representative stock photography and does not depict
      Reliant Construction projects, personnel, or job sites unless expressly labeled as such.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      The Reliant name, mark, and site content are owned by {site.legalName} or used with
      permission. You may not copy, reproduce, or use them for commercial purposes without our
      written consent.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Don't misuse the site: no interfering with its operation, no attempting to access
      non-public systems, no scraping at scale, and no submitting false or misleading
      inquiries.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Third-party links</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Links to third-party sites (including our sister company, Reliant Solar) are provided
      for convenience. We are not responsible for the content or practices of other sites.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Disclaimers and limitation of liability</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      This website is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind regarding the site
      itself. To the fullest extent permitted by law, {site.legalName} is not liable for
      damages arising from your use of the website. Nothing in these terms limits rights you
      have under a signed project agreement or rights that cannot be limited by law.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      These terms are governed by the laws of the State of New Jersey, without regard to
      conflict-of-law rules.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      We may update these terms from time to time; the version posted here with the latest
      effective date applies.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-3">
      {site.legalName}<br />
      {site.address.street}, {site.address.city}, {site.address.region} {site.address.zip}<br />
      <a href={site.phoneHref} class="font-semibold text-brand-deep hover:underline">{site.phoneDisplay}</a> ·
      <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`} class="font-semibold text-brand-deep hover:underline">{site.email}</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</LegalLayout>
